-- Oracle software sales beat its forecast
-- 
-- Thu Jun 23, 2011 4:12pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/06/23/us-oracle-idUSTRE75M75220110623

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - Oracle Corp's new software sales rose 15 percent during its fourth quarter ended May 31, beating its own forecasts of 4 percent to 14 percent growth. 

 The world's No. 3 software maker also reported profit, excluding items, of 75 cents per share, beating Wall Street estimates of 71 cents. (Reporting by  Jim Finkle ; Editing by  Bernard Orr )